      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): fall back to sendMessage when sendRichMessage unsupported by client",
        "body": "Fixes #93794\n\n## Summary\n\nWhen Telegram Bot API 10.1 `sendRichMessage` fails because the target client (e.g. Telegram Web) reports the message format as unsupported, fall back to regular `sendMessage` with HTML formatting. This ensures messages remain deliverable regardless of client compatibility.\n\n### Changes\n\n- **network-errors.ts**: New `isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError()` detection function\n- **bot/delivery.send.ts**: `sendTelegramText()` catches unsupported error, retries as HTML\n- **send.ts**: `sendChunkedText()` catches unsupported error, retries via regular chunk path; `editMessageTelegram` catches unsupported error on rich edit, falls back to standard HTML edit\n- **draft-stream.ts**: `sendRenderedMessage()` and `sendMessageTransportPreview()` catch unsupported error, retry as plain send/edit\n\n## ClawSweeper review findings addressed\n\n### [P1] Chunk replay guard — no duplication when partial rich chunks were already delivered\n\nPreviously, if `sendRichMessage` succeeded for chunk 1 but failed with unsupported on chunk 2, the outer catch would resend ALL content as HTML, duplicating chunk 1. \n\n**Fix**: `sendChunkedText` tracks each successfully sent rich chunk via a shared sentinel. On unsupported error, if any chunks were already delivered, the fallback is **skipped** (the error re-throws) instead of duplicating visible content. This handles the 99.9% case where the first rich chunk reveals the client doesn't support the format — in that case `sentCount === 0` and the full HTML fallback runs safely.\n\nTest: `does not fall back to HTML when some rich chunks were already delivered (no duplication)`\n\n```typescript\n// Chunk 1 succeeds, chunk 2 fails → no HTML fallback, error propagates\nexpect(sendRichMock).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2);\nexpect(botApi.sendMessage).not.toHaveBeenCalled();\n```\n\n### [P2] Durable rich edit path covered\n\n`editMessageTelegram` called `richRawApi.editMessageText` directly without unsupported error handling — opt-in rich edits could still fail silently.\n\n**Fix**: `performTextEdit` now catches `isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError` inside the rich API branch and falls through to the standard HTML `editMessageText` path, matching the same pattern used in `delivery.send.ts` and `draft-stream.ts`.\n\nTests: `falls back to standard editMessageText when rich edit returns unsupported`, `falls back for MESSAGE_UNSUPPORTED rich edit errors`, `does not fall back for non-unsupported rich edit errors`\n\n### [P2] Narrowed unsupported matcher\n\nThe `RICH_MESSAGE_UNSUPPORTED_RE` regex contained bare `UNSUPPORTED` as an alternative, which could match unrelated Telegram API errors (e.g. `UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE`) and convert them to HTML fallbacks, hiding real errors.\n\n**Fix**: Changed `UNSUPPORTED` to `UNSUPPORTED_MESSAGE`, keeping known error codes (`MESSAGE_UNSUPPORTED`, `UNSUPPORTED_MESSAGE_TYPE`) while rejecting non-message unsupported codes.\n\nTest: `rejects bare UNSUPPORTED without message context`\n\n```typescript\n// UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE and UNSUPPORTED_PARAM no longer match\nexpect(isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError(\"UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE\")).toBe(false);\nexpect(isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError(\"UNSUPPORTED_PARAM\")).toBe(false);\n```\n\n## Test evidence\n\nAll 313 tests pass across 4 test files (67 network-errors + 57 delivery + 50 draft-stream + 139 send):\n\n```\nTest Files  4 passed (4)\nTests  313 passed (313)\n```\n\nEach error classification, send path, edit path, and chunk scenario is covered by focused unit tests verifying:\n- `isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError` matches known Telegram Web error formats\n- Rejects parse errors, rate limits, server errors, and unrelated messages\n- `sendTelegramText` falls back from rich to HTML on unsupported\n- `sendChunkedText` falls back from rich to HTML on unsupported (first chunk)\n- `sendChunkedText` does NOT fall back when rich chunks were already delivered\n- `editMessageTelegram` falls back from rich edit to standard HTML edit on unsupported\n- `draft-stream` send and edit both fall back on unsupported\n- `deliverReplies` falls back from rich to standard send on unsupported\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: Telegram Web users receiving \"This message is currently not supported on Telegram Web\" after enabling `richMessages: true` — bot sends `sendRichMessage` format which Telegram Web cannot render\n- Real environment tested: local source checkout, Node.js v24.13.1, Linux x64\n- Evidence after fix: 313 unit tests pass verifying all error classifications, fallback paths, and edge cases. Three ClawSweeper findings addressed: chunk replay guard prevents visible duplication, durable rich edit path now falls back, and unsupported matcher is scoped to message-related errors only.\n- Terminal output:\n  ```\n  $ pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/network-errors.test.ts \\\n    extensions/telegram/src/bot/delivery.test.ts \\\n    extensions/telegram/src/draft-stream.test.ts \\\n    extensions/telegram/src/send.test.ts\n  \n  RUN  v4.1.8\n  \n  Test Files  4 passed (4)\n  Tests  313 passed (313)\n  Duration  28.51s\n  ```\n",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-rich-message-fallback",
